<h1>Policies</h1>
<h2>BLTBaseball.com-Privacy Policy</h2>
<p>As a youth organization we are very concerned about privacy. Therefore, we have taken measures to tailor our content and offerings to help protect an individual’s privacy. This Privacy Policy applies to information collected on this web site and our official page on Facebook, as well as information received from other sources such as enrollment and player records reporting.</p>

<h2>Advice to Children and Parents</h2>
<p>We strongly advise children to get their parent(s) or guardian(s) to review any information they intend to transmit and get their permission before submitting any kind of personal data to anyone over the Internet. We urge parents to seriously and repeatedly discuss with their children the danger of giving personal information to anyone (online or in person) whom they don't personally know. We also encourage parents and guardians to spend time online with their children monitoring and reviewing their children’s online activity. As a policy, no person under the age of 13 is permitted to register directly to receive Big League Travel Baseball League’s electronic communications.</p>

<h2>What personal information do we collect for our electronic database?</h2>
<p>Big League Travel Baseball, LLC requires registered Coaches to submit rosters. Rosters are required to include player information including date of birth, parent or guardian contact information and identifying information about each individual team’s coaches and manager. A player, manager or coach must be listed be on the roster submitted to Big League Travel Baseball OR iScrimmag.com. Rosters should be submitted through the “Teams” section on www.bltbaseball.com or www.iScrimmage.com . This is an easy way to provide the required data on players, managers and coaches, and ensures that Big League Travel Baseball receives the data that is required as noted above.</p>

The information provided on rosters is utilized by Big Leave Travel Baseball and iScrimmage.com in the following ways:
<ul class="list_doc">
    <li>To catalog and record each individual player into a yearly listing of participants in the program. These records are maintained in the Big League Travel Baseball archives and for historical purposes. This information may also be is used for operational issues that may arise with respect to eligibility of the participants in the Big League Travel Baseball league program.</li>

    <li>To maintain a record of the coaches and managers involved in the Big League Travel Baseball League program and their associated team and league. This information is used to provide seasonal training materials, to send the Big League Travel Baseball newsletter, for their team’s players during the season as well as operational issues that may arise requiring contact with Big League Travel Baseball.</li>

    <li>Email addresses provided to Big League Travel Baseball and iScrimmage.com through the league management system by each player’s parent(s) or guardian(s), and coach and/or manager are incorporated into Big League Travel Baseball’s electronic database for the current season. The privacy policy below describes our process for collecting and using email addresses of our constituents.</li>


    <li>Household mailing addresses reported on rosters are occasionally used to provide information to those residents about the Big League Travel Baseball and iScrimmage.com League program. Should information be sent, it will be sent under the cover of “Current Resident” or “To the Parent or Guardian of Big League Travel Baseball Participant.”</li>
</ul>
<p>At Big League Travel Baseball, we collect information in addition to players and coaches’ data in order to help identify you and/or your child’s interests in the Big League Travel Baseball and iScrimmage.com programs and the associated League with which you may be affiliated. On our web sites you can read articles, view discussion boards, enter contests, participate in promotions, express your opinion, shop online or subscribe to our online portals, emails and newsletters. The only time we will ask for personal or contact information from you will be:</p>
<ul class="list_doc">
<li>1. to provide you with information that you’ve requested based on your selected preferences;</li>
<li>2. to enable us to respond to your inquiry;</li>
<li>3. to register you for a contest or promotion;</li>
<li>4. to take your subscription for a Big League Travel Baseball publication or web-based portal, or;</li>
<li>5. to obtain operational contact information.</li>
</ul>
<p>If you do not want your personal information collected, even for these reasons, please do not submit it to us. You also have the opportunity to “Unsubscribe” to any Big League Travel Baseball or iScrimmage.com controlled electronic large group communication at any time by clicking on the Safe Unsubscribe™ link at the bottom of any email you receive from us.</p>
<h2>How do we use personal information collected and received</h2>
<p>Any information gathered by Big League Travel Baseball on this website, through the League management system and/or any other means, will be used for the sole purpose of furthering the mission of Big League Travel Baseball, LLC. Big League Travel Baseball, LLC does not sell any information collected from you to outside companies but we may provide special offers or services through Big League Travel Baseball, LLC and/or its sponsors, licensees or other business associates.</p>
<p>We also may use the information you provide to fulfill your requests for information or products or to respond to your inquiries about our program. We sometimes use this information to communicate with you, such as to update you on new rules and regulations, notify you when you have won a contest, or provide you with the latest news story being covered by Big League Travel Baseball, LLC. The information you provide in connection with our online forums, social media sites and communities is used to create an interactive experience. We may use this information to facilitate conversation and from time to time, offer you products, programs and services.</p>
<p>Should you receive information from Big League Travel Baseball or one of our partners, this information will be clearly identified with Big League Travel Baseball, LLC or iScrimmage.com identification marks in adherence with our trademark registration.</p>
<p>Please note that some information you receive may direct you to a non-Big League Travel Baseball web site to participate in a contest or promotion. Please refer to these web sites for specific Privacy Policies and use of data as we have no control over information that is submitted to, or collected by, these third parties.
We may be required to share your personal information and non-personal information pursuant to judicial or governmental subpoenas, warrants, or orders. If we are required to do so, we will, of course, obey the law. In addition, notwithstanding any term to the contrary in this Privacy Policy, we reserve the right to use, disclose, and/or share your personal and non-personal information in order to investigate, prevent, or take action regarding illegal activities, suspected fraud, situations involving potential threats to the physical safety of any person, violations of this Website's Terms of Use or as otherwise required by law.</p>

<h2>Contest Submissions and Promotions</h2>
